        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/denial-of-service",
          "message": {
            "text": "The Guardrails Service is vulnerable to resource exhaustion via high-volume prompt submission. An attacker sends computationally expensive prompts (complex regex evaluation patterns, adversarially crafted inputs that maximize rule evaluation cost) at high rate to degrade or collapse the filtering pipeline.",
            "markdown": "Implement per-IP and per-session rate limiting at the network ingress (before the Guardrails Service). Apply a computational complexity budget per prompt evaluation; reject prompts that exceed the budget. Use asynchronous processing queues with backpressure to prevent synchronous overload."
