        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/repudiation",
          "message": {
            "text": "The Clinical Advisory Sub-Agent denies having generated a specific clinical summary or recommendation. Without non-repudiable logs of each clinical output (with content hash and the KB documents retrieved to produce it), clinical decisions influenced by sub-agent outputs cannot be attributed, and the sub-agent cannot be held accountable for hallucinated or incorrect recommendations.",
            "markdown": "Log every clinical output produced by the Clinical Advisory Sub-Agent to the Audit Logger with: (a) the clinical query received (content hash), (b) the KB document IDs and hashes retrieved, (c) the full clinical summary content hash, (d) a signature using the sub-agent's service key. Log the Clinical Decision Log Entry atomically before the summary is returned to the Orchestrator."
          },
